This is the first move that is out of opening book.  Three systems stem from here.  g3 fianchetto variation, Nd2 Nimzovich (Knight's tour) variation, and Bg5 Uhlmann variation.  Bf4 scores well in the world db and is played later most of the time with Bg5.

Here we reach a climax in development.  I make a move which I had mixed feeling about, seen next move.  Whites main ace in the whole is his center but black will have great chances with a queen side attack.  Notice that the move called for in the position e5 loses the d5 pawn.  Best would probably be Rd1 or Bc2.
